name: Rumah Kost Gumitish Banyuning Singaraja Buleleng
address: Banyuning, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1: Reception was confusing as there is no office or obvious place to find any caretaker, so we milled around the front for several minutes next to an aggressive dog in a cage before someone came down. Maybe it was a bad room I looked at, but I found it small and dark. The bathroom smelled very bad so I didn't stay. For those wanting to stay here, maybe check the room first before booking.
review 2: I stayed here for one year during the pandemic time. The room where I stayed was really nice and air conditioned. There was also a nice balcony where I loved to sit. I really enjoyed the privacy and I felt really safe. The wifi is also really good and the host is also really nice and helpful. Furthermore there are lots of warung and facilities in the neighborhood and you are really close to the city. I am really sad I had to leave but I hope to come back soon.
review 3:
We stayed there 2016 for some months for a really fair price and the buildings looks very new.
The family who owns this place is so friendly and welcoming.
Specially the grandmother was always joking around with her older friends and just Lough a lot.
Sure it is a kost so if you are a foreigners like we maybe better inform yourself first what it is but we really appreciate this opportunity to stay there and had a great time so close together with the locals and not in a big hotel.
Terima kasih
